results.title: A Legion Quest Addendum: An Hour of Last Things
results.description: Cable spends some time with the X-Men and has a few intimate moments with Domino as the world ends.

results.title: Lost Souls
results.description: Domino vs. Grizzly, Death of Grizzly, Cable returns to future w/ Jenskot.

results.title: The Long Way Home
results.description: Cable and Dom return from the future smack in the middle of a war between the Expatriates and the Genoshian Press Gang.

results.title: Rebels
results.description: Teams w/Domino vs. Sugar Man, origin of Genosha.

results.title: Tick...Tick...Tick!
results.description: With a nuclear device ready to detonate in the heart of Genosha, Cable has to figure out how to stop the bomb and Sugarman at the same time; Mr. Sinister becomes aware of Sugarman and his genetic manipulations; Sugarman becomes aware that there is an alternate Nate Grey running around.

results.title: Man in the Mirror
results.description: The X-Men and Cable learn of the existance and powerful threat of Nate Grey--X-Man; Cable leaves to confront him.

results.title: Twenty Questions
results.description: Cable/Kane reflect, Sinsear searches for Weasel/Deadpool/Mr. Tolliver, G.W. Bridge searches for Cable.

results.title: For Every Action...
results.description: Cable and X-Man finally meet and duke it out as their proximity with each other causes confusion and pain to both; Exodus shows up to suck up the energy.

results.title: Mapping the Mission
results.description: A brief history of Cable up to this point.

results.title: ...There is a Reaction!
results.description: Cable and X-Man engage in a final violent conflict, and Cable goes against Blaquesmith's warnings and saves Nate Grey's life rather than killing his alternate self from a forgotten timeline.

results.title: Mapping the Mission Part Two
results.description: The second installment of Cable's history up to the present day.

results.title: The Askani' Son & Domino--On the Path of Onslaught!
Venting
results.description: Coping with his son's death at the hands of Wolverine, Cable and Dom try to track down Onslaught while being observed by Post; Onslaught attempts to take Blaquesmith out.

results.title: Never is a Very Short Time
results.description: Investigating Blaquesmith's apparent death, Cable runs up against Post and remembers the time he first met and saved the powerful mutant.

results.title: Loose Cannons
results.description: Cable and Storm face down an Onslaught controlled Hulk and end up reverting him to his savage, mindless form.

results.title: It Is Always Darkest...
results.description: Apocalypse and Cable travel to the astral plane to confront Onslaught directly; Invisible Woman comes along to try and save her son from Onslaught's evil plans for him; Onslaught punts them all out of his fortress easily.

X-Men: The Complete Onslaught Epic Book 3 (Trade Paperback)

results.title: The Gift
results.description: In the wake of Onslaught, Nathanial Richards tries to save Cable from his devastating injuries; Cable talks to his wife and son in the netherworld compliments of young Franklin.

X-Men: The Complete Onslaught Epic Book 4 (Trade Paperback)

results.title: True Lies
results.description: Kane calls Cable for help as he has picked up a mysterious attacker; The attacker turns out to be Psycho-Man who wants his cybernetics to create an army of soldiers in the Microverse; The villain attempts a kidnapping but picks up Copycat disguised as Kane instead of the real deal; Cable and crew head into the Microverse.

results.title: In Perspective
results.description: Cable, Cane and the Micronauts try to save Vanessa from Psycho-Man.

results.title: All Things Great And Small
results.description: Round two against the Psycho-Man for our miniature heroes.

results.title: A Leader Among Men
results.description: Cable Vs. reunited Six-Pack

results.title: Into the Dark
results.description: Cable and company try to save Renee Majcomb from Bastion's First Strike team.

results.title: Tolerance
results.description: Marrow and Callisto crash a Lila Cheney concert where Cable is forcing himself to try and have a good time.

results.title: Broken Soldiers
results.description: Ch'Vayre tells his Acolytes a story of Cable in the future.

results.title: Temptation in the Wilderness
results.description: Cable confronts his mother on the astral plane where she tempts him to join her.

results.title: Moving Target Part One: No Escape
results.description: Bastion has taken over X-Mansion and Cable invades to protect Xavier's files and to break Caliban out.

results.title: Moving Target Part Two: Siege
results.description: Cable and Caliban have to bust out of X-Mansion past Zero Tolerance; Cable goes back in to download and destroy Xavier's files on mutants but takes a little too long as Bastion bursts in on him.

results.title: Cover #24270
results.description: Cable finally comes face to face with Bastion!

results.title: Moving Target Part Three: Man-to-Man
results.description: Cable has it out with Bastion and lives to tell the tale.

results.title: From Out Of The Fire...A Savior!
The Hellfire Hunt Part 1: Dirty Secrets
results.description: Tabloid journalist Irene Merryweather is targeted by the Hellfire Club for investigating a story about Sebastian Shaw; Cable intervenes.

results.title: And He Shall Know Death's Touch !
The Hellfire Hunt Part 2: Weary Knights and Shabby Paladins
results.description: Cable breaks into the Hellfire Club to figure out what Shaw and Pierce are up to and runs up against Paladin.

results.title: Sinsearly Yours Sincerely Mine...
results.description: Cable is teleported to Sinsear's base to have a showdown with his old enemy; After the fight, Cable learns that Tolliver is still alive.

results.title: The Hellfire Hunt Part 3: And He Shall Be Called...Man !
The Hellfire Hunt Part 4: Faith and Deception
results.description: Cable travels to Switzerland to find one of his safehouses tended by the Nazi criminal Master Man; The Hellfire Club moves into position.

results.title: The Hellfire Hunt Part 5: Beyond Belief
results.description: Master Man Dies Helping Cable Find the Hellfire Club; Shaw and Pierce Launch a Frontal Assault on Apocalypse's Fortress.

results.title: To Breach the Lair of Apocalypse!
The Hellfire Hunt Part 6: Beautiful Friend
results.description: Cable confronts Pierce and Shaw in Apocalypse's fortress for an explosive finale.

results.title: Jungle Action
results.description: After the battle with Pierce, Cable crash lands in Wakanda where he becomes a guest of the Black Panther; Klaw invades Wakanda to repair his vibranium sonic blaster.

results.title: Domino's Back--But Is It For The Last Time?
Wiser Times
results.description: Cable sets up shop in Hell's Kitchen; Irene finds Cable eating in a diner flirting with a waitress; Domino and Cable break things off.

results.title: Blood Rite
results.description: Domino is taken down by a bounty hunter, and Cable seeks revenge.

results.title: Momentary Lapse
results.description: Cable rescues Blaquesmith from Rama Tut; Cable's powers are weakened by a battle going on in the psychic plane.

results.title: Lest They Shed Blood In His Name!
Busted!
results.description: Cable retrieves a weapon from Ch'Vayre's disciples to focus his diminished powers and disbands the acolytes; SHIELD prepares to capture Cable; The techno organic virus runs unchecked in Cable since his TK doesn't work.

results.title: The Nemesis Contract Part 1: The Wrath of Zzzax!
results.description: THE NEMESIS CONTRACT PART 1 Cable’s body continues to deteriorate from the techno-virus due to his lack of telepathy. With new threats on the horizon, will Cable train until he’s maxed out? Agent Jack Truman continues to dig up dirt on Cable, while Zzzax makes his presence known in Hell’s Kitchen! Can Cable defeat two foes in one fell swoop?

results.title: The Nemesis Contract Part 1: Pressure Points
results.description: Shield commissions Agent 18 to take down Cable; Agent 18 uses Zzzax to flush Cable out into the open.

results.title: Fathers and Sons Act One: Sunset Breaks
results.description: Tyler Dayspring, Cable's son, stands revealed as Mr. Tolliver; Cable and Domino meet at Maddie Pryor's grave where they are confronted by Sinister; Sinister explains that Cable is the original and Stryfe is the copy; Askani is sent back in time to assist but is captured by Tyler; Cable is possessed by Stryfe; Jean realizes that Stryfe is back and his purpose is to kill her and her husband.

results.title: The Nemesis Contract Part 2: Introducing Agent 18
results.description: THE NEMESIS CONTRACT PART 2 Introducing Agent 18, Jack Truman! Irene Merryweather and Blaquesmith become concerned for Cable after witnessing Agent 18’s incursion in Hell’s Kitchen. Why does Jack Truman want Cable dead? And to what lengths will he go to ensure a successful mission?

results.title: The Nemesis Contract Part 2: Atlas Burned
results.description: Agent 18 and Cable battle in Hells Kitchen, while the techno organic virus eats Cable alive.

results.title: The Nemesis Contract Part 3: Captive of Shield
results.description: THE NEMESIS CONTRACT PART 3 What is on S.H.I.E.L.D.’s agenda when it comes to Cable? And will the peacekeeping task force make their motives known? A surprising twist will leave Cable questioning who, if anyone, he should trust.

results.title: The Nemesis Contract Part 3: Captive Audience
results.description: Shield extracts some of the techno organic virus from a captured Cable and inserts it into the Nemesis Robots; Agent 18 finds out what is really going on and frees Cable; Cable gets his powers back.

results.title: The Nemesis Contract Part 4: Howling Commandos!
results.description: THE NEMESIS CONTRACT PART 4 Nick Fury and his Howling Commandos make an electrifying appearance in the conclusion to Nemesis Contract! Will Cable be able to restore his trust in S.H.I.E.L.D.? Cable and Nick Fury unite forces in a team-up unlike any you’ve seen before!

results.title: The Nemesis Contract Part 4: Strange Agencies
results.description: The techno virus enhanced Nemesis Robots attack the Helicarrier thinking themselves to be Fury and his Howling Commandos fighting a bunch of Nazis; Cable has a final confrontation with Agent 18; Irene writes an expose of the whole affair for the Daily Bugle.

results.title: Blood Brothers Part 2: From the Past--Stryfe!
